(window.webpackJsonp=window.webpackJsonp||[]).push([[46],{305:function(module,exports){module.exports={compilerOutput:[],storyContent:{inkVersion:19,root:[[{"->t->":"chapter_17_contenders_and_adversaries_intro"},{"->t->":"yield"},{"->t->":"chapter_17_contenders_and_adversaries_recollection"},{"->t->":"yield"},{"->t->":"chapter_17_contenders_and_adversaries_planning"},{"->t->":"yield"},{"->t->":"chapter_17_contenders_and_adversaries_dancing_and_blood"},{"->t->":"yield"},{"->t->":"chapter_17_contenders_and_adversaries_holy_fire"},{"->t->":"yield"},{"->t->":"chapter_17_contenders_and_adversaries_immanent_escape"},"ev","str","^","/str","/ev",{"->":"done"},["done",{"#f":5,"#n":"g-0"}],null],"done",{chapter_17_contenders_and_adversaries_intro:['^<play-sound group="music" name="breakpoint" />',"\n","^<p>","\n","^You knew for years it was coming. The end of the world sounded like plastic scraping against itself, people afraid to breathe His air or even touch their own doorknobs, mad shouts outside your bedroom window, dogs howling down the boulevards with no owners ever to follow, months in which every person spoke the exact same words about plague and warfare.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^The end of the world is heartbreaking and boring, but you knew to listen for the trumpets, to watch for the signs, all the final and foundational glyphs, numbers and codes appearing in sixes, unnoticed in the light of dawn.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^The sleep of reason may breed monsters, but the slumber of faith is a betrayal still more grave.","\n","^</p>","\n","ev","void","/ev","->->",{"#f":1}],chapter_17_contenders_and_adversaries_recollection:["^<p>","\n","^The day Wormwood came to Albi, you were watching from the distant blue peaks, through spyglass and wire. Its heat was on your face. Its light was inside your eyes. You watched as good young men and women were burned in the manner of infected cattle. A false sacrifice to enrage the Archon, an attempt to bleed Him of decency.","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->t->":"yield"},"^<p>","\n","^It will not work. He is above such ploys. Men can lose faith. You did, once, staring up at a different nation's flag, learning a history that was not yours, surveying the periodic truths, finding no space for faith. You recovered, but His flock may not.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^They are lost in the whorl of apocalypse, a palimpsest scraped by layer, unveiling blinding light at last. Those who who have not yet lost all, who have not found, within His grace, more than they ever had, are paralyzed by visions of His thought.","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->t->":"yield"},"^<p>","\n","^What is needed is sacrifice, sympathetic and resonant, white overtop black, moving ahead of the waveform by half a step, cancelling it in total.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^The nature of opposite and identical actions has been known since the before times. Even those impoverished heretics who labored before the Archon was known and victorious, before the holy land was rendered safe, understood such things.","\n","^</p>","\n","ev","void","/ev","->->",{"#f":1}],chapter_17_contenders_and_adversaries_planning:["^<p>","\n","^In Capital, filled with grace, you have come to accepted the underlying complexities of all laws, even the Archon's. Suicide is a mortal sin, murder equally so, and we all know the attention of the media is only caught by acts of violence, but <em>martyrdom is glory</em>.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^One must only be sure their death matters enough. Then they may choose it. To acknowledge this fact is only grace with an ultimate price, not heresy. The goal is to write terror on the body, to plunge headlong into pyroclastic agony with the grace of a saint, fanning the flames with palms.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^The plan is to pay homage to Stephen. To be a protomartyr for a land progressed beyond memory.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^To finally render unto the Archon that which is His, and should have remained always such.","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->t->":"yield"},"^<p>","\n",'^Now you are here, standing before a grand dove, sculpted in dark steel. It is 1100. You have the can of kerosene, still good after dark years in dust and mold. One squarish metal lighter with the stamp of the Archon, blessed be, on its obverse, His creed on its reverse. The beat-up old stereo, with one single track loaded: "I Apologize For The Inconvenience," a long-time favorite, great for multimodal dances.',"\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^And what could be more multifarious than ascendance in gorgeous martyrdom?","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->t->":"yield"},"^<p>","\n","^Now you are here, kneeling in prayer. Three rough stones anchor you inside a pyramid of invisible light. It's 1111.","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->t->":"yield"},"^<p>","\n","^Onlookers gather in the square, vaguely curious, keeping back meters still. Some are familiar faces, and know to expect your dancing in town, on the parkland field before the library.","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->t->":"yield"},"^<p>","\n","^Now you are here. It's 1115. You begin the dance, whirling in place, and the world bleeds into a single gapless panorama.","\n","^</p>","\n","ev","void","/ev","->->",{"#f":1}],chapter_17_contenders_and_adversaries_dancing_and_blood:['^<stop-sound group="music" name="breakpoint" />',"\n","^<p>","\n","^At first there is just the sound of fabric spinning, and the holy mantra.","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->t->":"yield"},'^<play-sound group="music" name="i-apologize-for-the-inconvenience" />',"\n","^<p>","\n","^The song will begin after a programmed delay.","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->t->":"yield"},"^<blockquote>","\n","^<p>","\n","^He is great.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^HE is great.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^He IS great. He IS great.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^He is GREAT. He is GREAT. He is GREAT.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^HE IS GREAT. HE IS GREAT. HE IS GREAT. HE IS GREAT. HE IS GREAT.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^HEISGREAT. HEISGREAT. HEISGREAT. HEISGREAT. HEISGREAT. HEISGREAT. HEISGREAT. HEISGREAT.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^HEISGREATHEISGREATHEISGREAT. HEISGREATHEISGREATHEISGREAT. HEISGREATHEISGREATHEISGREAT. HEISGREATHEISGREATHEISGREAT. HEISGREAT.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^HEISGREATHEISGREATHEISGREATHEISGREATHEISGREATHEISGREATHEISGREATHEISGREATHEISGREATHEISGREATHEISGREATHEISGREATHEISGREATHEISGREATHEISGREATHEISGREATHEISGREATHEISGREATHEISGREATHEISGREATHEISGREAT!","\n","^</p>","\n","^</blockquote>","\n","ev","void","/ev","->->",{"#f":1}],chapter_17_contenders_and_adversaries_holy_fire:["^<p>","\n","^Now you are here. It's 1120.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^You cover yourself in the stink of death recovered, and you set its energies free.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^You become a star, a sun, the crowd your satellites, roving long ellipses around the terror or darting in to attempt a Samaritan embrace.","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->t->":"yield"},"^<p>","\n","^But the dance is too fast, the divine zeal too fierce, and each time they retreat.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^Let the volcanic essence of the Archon's will ride through all your cells, on a chariot made of diamonds. One last time. Let there be light. Let it be bright. Let it be as great as He.","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->t->":"yield"},"^<p>","\n","^Now you are here, a pillar of holy fire. It's 1121.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^A single man, barely visible through dying eyes, boiling sclera. Signals now barely received by the outmoded meat. He runs towards you. An LEO? A hero? Both and neither.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^Nothing but the soul will be certain again.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^It needn't be.","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->t->":"yield"},"^<p>","\n","^You feel yourself falling back to earth from a great height.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^The man rotates your body, arms and jacket wrapped tight. You can feel, with your last neural sparks, your skin fusing into his jacket. Two incandescent souls melting to one column of ardor.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^The tower of flames reaches its nadir, snuffed.","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->t->":"yield"},"^<p>","\n","^The man begins to rise, wounded, unsteady, smoke rising from his gallant skin.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^The moment the breath of highest wisdom comes to your charred and mewling lungs, as soon as he shifts his weeping body off yours, the monolith of God bursts forth once more.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^Seeking the heavens. Striking along a single line of flight to the arms of the patriarch who heals all wounds.","\n","^</p>","\n","ev","void","/ev","->->",{"#f":1}],chapter_17_contenders_and_adversaries_immanent_escape:["^<p>","\n","^Now you are here. The smartest watches and glowing tablets read 1122. The immanent time-keeping crystal of your heart says it is <bdi>\u05d0\u05dc\u05e3</bdi>, soundless and before days were crafted.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^You soar over all, a speechless dream, wings of pure light, beyond strength and courage, caroling in every fatherly tongue ever known beneath the stars.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^The first Father opens His arms. You are pulled into His heart, becoming a portion of Him. You live as love with Him in Alltime.","\n","^</p>","\n","ev","void","/ev","->->",{"#f":1}],yield:[["ev","str","^\u25fc","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0",flg:4},{"c-0":["\n",{"->":".^.^.g-0"},{"#f":5}],"g-0":["ev","void","/ev","->->",{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],done:[{"temp=":"out_var"},[["ev",{"VAR?":"out_var"},"/ev",{"->":".^.b",c:!0},{b:["\n","ev",{"VAR?":"out_var"},"/ev",{"VAR=":"XLR8R_OUT_PASSAGE",re:!0},{"->":"done.1.1"},null]}],"nop","\n","ev","str","^\u25fc","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0",flg:20},{"c-0":["\n",{"->":".^.^.g-0"},{"#f":5}],"g-0":['^<stop-sound group="music" name="i-apologize-for-the-inconvenience" />',"\n","done",{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"global decl":["ev","str","^XLR8R_PREVIOUS_VALUE","/str",{"VAR=":"DEBUG"},"str","^chapter-18","/str",{"VAR=":"XLR8R_OUT_PASSAGE"},"str","^XLR8R_PREVIOUS_VALUE","/str",{"VAR=":"XLR8R_NEW_GAME"},"str","^XLR8R_PREVIOUS_VALUE","/str",{"VAR=":"confused_score"},"str","^XLR8R_PREVIOUS_VALUE","/str",{"VAR=":"convert_score"},"str","^XLR8R_PREVIOUS_VALUE","/str",{"VAR=":"resister_score"},"/ev","end",null],"#f":1}],listDefs:{}},text:'VAR DEBUG = "XLR8R_PREVIOUS_VALUE"\r\n\r\nVAR XLR8R_OUT_PASSAGE = "chapter-18"\r\n\r\nVAR XLR8R_NEW_GAME = "XLR8R_PREVIOUS_VALUE"\r\n\r\nVAR confused_score = "XLR8R_PREVIOUS_VALUE"\r\nVAR convert_score = "XLR8R_PREVIOUS_VALUE"\r\nVAR resister_score = "XLR8R_PREVIOUS_VALUE"\r\n\r\n\r\n-> chapter_17_contenders_and_adversaries_intro ->\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n-> chapter_17_contenders_and_adversaries_recollection ->\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n-> chapter_17_contenders_and_adversaries_planning ->\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n-> chapter_17_contenders_and_adversaries_dancing_and_blood ->\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n-> chapter_17_contenders_and_adversaries_holy_fire ->\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n-> chapter_17_contenders_and_adversaries_immanent_escape ->\r\n\r\n-> done("")\r\n\r\n\r\n=== chapter_17_contenders_and_adversaries_intro ===\r\n<play-sound group="music" name="breakpoint" />\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nYou knew for years it was coming. The end of the world sounded like plastic scraping against itself, people afraid to breathe His air or even touch their own doorknobs, mad shouts outside your bedroom window, dogs howling down the boulevards with no owners ever to follow, months in which every person spoke the exact same words about plague and warfare.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThe end of the world is heartbreaking and boring, but you knew to listen for the trumpets, to watch for the signs, all the final and foundational glyphs, numbers and codes appearing in sixes, unnoticed in the light of dawn.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThe sleep of reason may breed monsters, but the slumber of faith is a betrayal still more grave.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n->->\r\n\r\n\r\n=== chapter_17_contenders_and_adversaries_recollection ===\r\n<p>\r\nThe day Wormwood came to Albi, you were watching from the distant blue peaks, through spyglass and wire. Its heat was on your face. Its light was inside your eyes. You watched as good young men and women were burned in the manner of infected cattle. A false sacrifice to enrage the Archon, an attempt to bleed Him of decency.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nIt will not work. He is above such ploys. Men can lose faith. You did, once, staring up at a different nation\'s flag, learning a history that was not yours, surveying the periodic truths, finding no space for faith. You recovered, but His flock may not.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThey are lost in the whorl of apocalypse, a palimpsest scraped by layer, unveiling blinding light at last. Those who who have not yet lost all, who have not found, within His grace, more than they ever had, are paralyzed by visions of His thought.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nWhat is needed is sacrifice, sympathetic and resonant, white overtop black, moving ahead of the waveform by half a step, cancelling it in total.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThe nature of opposite and identical actions has been known since the before times. Even those impoverished heretics who labored before the Archon was known and victorious, before the holy land was rendered safe, understood such things.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n->->\r\n\r\n\r\n=== chapter_17_contenders_and_adversaries_planning ===\r\n<p>\r\nIn Capital, filled with grace, you have come to accepted the underlying complexities of all laws, even the Archon\'s. Suicide is a mortal sin, murder equally so, and we all know the attention of the media is only caught by acts of violence, but <em>martyrdom is glory</em>.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nOne must only be sure their death matters enough. Then they may choose it. To acknowledge this fact is only grace with an ultimate price, not heresy. The goal is to write terror on the body, to plunge headlong into pyroclastic agony with the grace of a saint, fanning the flames with palms.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThe plan is to pay homage to Stephen. To be a protomartyr for a land progressed beyond memory.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nTo finally render unto the Archon that which is His, and should have remained always such.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nNow you are here, standing before a grand dove, sculpted in dark steel. It is 1100. You have the can of kerosene, still good after dark years in dust and mold. One squarish metal lighter with the stamp of the Archon, blessed be, on its obverse, His creed on its reverse. The beat-up old stereo, with one single track loaded: "I Apologize For The Inconvenience," a long-time favorite, great for multimodal dances.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nAnd what could be more multifarious than ascendance in gorgeous martyrdom?\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nNow you are here, kneeling in prayer. Three rough stones anchor you inside a pyramid of invisible light. It\'s 1111.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nOnlookers gather in the square, vaguely curious, keeping back meters still. Some are familiar faces, and know to expect your dancing in town, on the parkland field before the library.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nNow you are here. It\'s 1115. You begin the dance, whirling in place, and the world bleeds into a single gapless panorama.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n->->\r\n\r\n\r\n=== chapter_17_contenders_and_adversaries_dancing_and_blood ===\r\n<stop-sound group="music" name="breakpoint" />\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nAt first there is just the sound of fabric spinning, and the holy mantra.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n<play-sound group="music" name="i-apologize-for-the-inconvenience" />\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThe song will begin after a programmed delay.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n// 1, 1, 2, 3, 5, 8, 13...\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p>\r\nHe is great.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nHE is great.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nHe IS great. He IS great.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nHe is GREAT. He is GREAT. He is GREAT.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nHE IS GREAT. HE IS GREAT. HE IS GREAT. HE IS GREAT. HE IS GREAT.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nHEISGREAT. HEISGREAT. HEISGREAT. HEISGREAT. HEISGREAT. HEISGREAT. HEISGREAT. HEISGREAT.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nHEISGREATHEISGREATHEISGREAT. HEISGREATHEISGREATHEISGREAT. HEISGREATHEISGREATHEISGREAT. HEISGREATHEISGREATHEISGREAT. HEISGREAT.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nHEISGREATHEISGREATHEISGREATHEISGREATHEISGREATHEISGREATHEISGREATHEISGREATHEISGREATHEISGREATHEISGREATHEISGREATHEISGREATHEISGREATHEISGREATHEISGREATHEISGREATHEISGREATHEISGREATHEISGREATHEISGREAT!\r\n</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n->->\r\n\r\n\r\n=== chapter_17_contenders_and_adversaries_holy_fire ===\r\n<p>\r\nNow you are here. It\'s 1120.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nYou cover yourself in the stink of death recovered, and you set its energies free.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nYou become a star, a sun, the crowd your satellites, roving long ellipses around the terror or darting in to attempt a Samaritan embrace.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nBut the dance is too fast, the divine zeal too fierce, and each time they retreat.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nLet the volcanic essence of the Archon\'s will ride through all your cells, on a chariot made of diamonds. One last time. Let there be light. Let it be bright. Let it be as great as He.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nNow you are here, a pillar of holy fire. It\'s 1121.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nA single man, barely visible through dying eyes, boiling sclera. Signals now barely received by the outmoded meat. He runs towards you. An LEO? A hero? Both and neither.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nNothing but the soul will be certain again.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nIt needn\'t be.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nYou feel yourself falling back to earth from a great height.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThe man rotates your body, arms and jacket wrapped tight. You can feel, with your last neural sparks, your skin fusing into his jacket. Two incandescent souls melting to one column of ardor.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThe tower of flames reaches its nadir, snuffed.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThe man begins to rise, wounded, unsteady, smoke rising from his gallant skin.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThe moment the breath of highest wisdom comes to your charred and mewling lungs, as soon as he shifts his weeping body off yours, the monolith of God bursts forth once more.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nSeeking the heavens. Striking along a single line of flight to the arms of the patriarch who heals all wounds.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n->->\r\n\r\n\r\n=== chapter_17_contenders_and_adversaries_immanent_escape ===\r\n<p>\r\nNow you are here. The smartest watches and glowing tablets read 1122. The immanent time-keeping crystal of your heart says it is <bdi>\u05d0\u05dc\u05e3</bdi>, soundless and before days were crafted.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nYou soar over all, a speechless dream, wings of pure light, beyond strength and courage, caroling in every fatherly tongue ever known beneath the stars.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThe first Father opens His arms. You are pulled into His heart, becoming a portion of Him. You live as love with Him in Alltime.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n->->\r\n\r\n\r\n=== yield ===\r\n+ [\u25fc]\r\n-\r\n\r\n->->\r\n\r\n\r\n=== done(out_var) ===\r\n{\r\n\t- out_var:\r\n\t\t~ XLR8R_OUT_PASSAGE = out_var\r\n}\r\n\r\n* [\u25fc]\r\n-\r\n\r\n<stop-sound group="music" name="i-apologize-for-the-inconvenience" />\r\n\r\n-> DONE'}}}]);